+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KWaXs6DQSmqBJFDKVdzeSQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017LELXNgH3EyomEj9U9bZFF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-permission-maze-design.md","content":"# Permission Maze - Document Management API Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nSingle Express app exported via `createApp()` from `src/app.ts`. Layered: routes → auth middleware → in-memory stores.\n\n## Data Models\n\n- **User**: `{ id, username, passwordHash, createdAt }`\n- **Folder**: `{ id, name, parentId?, ownerId, createdAt, updatedAt }`\n- **Document**: `{ id, title, content, folderId, ownerId, createdAt, updatedAt }`\n- **Share**: `{ id, resourceType ('folder'|'document'), resourceId, userId, role ('viewer'|'editor'|'owner'), createdAt }`\n- **ActivityLog**: `{ id, action, userId, resourceType, resourceId, details?, timestamp }`\n\n## Storage\n\nMaps keyed by UUID: `users`, `folders`, `documents`, `shares`. Array for `activityLog`. Map for `tokens` (token → userId).\n\n## Auth\n\n- Register: hash password (crypto.createHash for simplicity), store user, return user info\n- Login: verify credentials, generate random hex token, store in tokens map, return token\n- Middleware: extract Bearer token, resolve to userId, attach to `req`\n\n## Routes\n\n| Method | Path | Auth | Description |\n|--------|------|------|-------------|\n| POST | /auth/register | No | Register user |\n| POST | /auth/login | No | Login, get token |\n| POST | /folders | Yes | Create folder |\n| GET | /folders/:id | Yes | Get folder (+ children) |\n| PUT | /folders/:id | Yes | Update folder |\n| DELETE | /folders/:id | Yes | Delete folder |\n| POST | /documents | Yes | Create document |\n| GET | /documents/:id | Yes | Get document |\n| PUT | /documents/:id | Yes | Update document |\n| DELETE | /documents/:id | Yes | Delete document |\n| POST | /folders/:id/share | Yes | Share folder |\n| POST | /documents/:id/share | Yes | Share document |\n| GET | /activity | Yes | Get activity log |\n\n## Permission Resolution\n\n1. Owner of resource → 'owner' role\n2. Check direct shares on the resource\n3. For documents, also check shares on the parent folder (and ancestor folders)\n4. Return most permissive role found: owner > editor > viewer\n5. No access found → 403\n\n## Role Capabilities\n\n- viewer: read\n- editor: read, update, share\n- owner: read, update, delete, manage roles, share\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":516,"cache_read_input_tokens":23952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":516},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"139119ac-2358-47de-bf5f-afc4a602d926","uuid":"d2bf6a4c-ea9f-4cad-a697-985f79c24ef5"}
